            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "On unix-likes the `detach` is necessary for the child process to get its own process group, which is necessary for it and its descendants to be killable as one unit. I am not sure how Windows behaves, with or without it, I only copied the existing behavior (from `libuv_proc_spawn`)",
