            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk I didn't realize there was a different implementation of `os_proc_tree_kill` for windows, so I assumed that passing `-pid` to uv_kill would just \"do the right thing\" there, but it doesn't, and that's what was causing the test failure. It's fixed now, and the patch isn't touching the windows path at all anymore.\r\n\r\nThe implementation of `os_proc_tree_kill` for windows calls win32 directly and as such it would be difficult to rewrite in Lua for `vim.system`. It would indeed be ideal if it just started calling the C functions.",
